HEADWORD: Peneplain
<hw>Pe"ne*plain`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>paene</ets>, <ets>pene</ets>, almost + E. <ets>plain</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Phys. Geog.)</fld> <def>A land surface reduced by erosion to the
general condition of a plain, but not wholly devoid of hills; a
base-level plain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

